{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.107",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 107,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 107 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:1",
      "text": "Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good, for his loving kindness endures forever.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:2",
      "text": "Let the redeemed by Yahweh say so, whom he has redeemed from the hand of the adversary,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:3",
      "text": "and gathered out of the lands, from the east and from the west, from the north and from the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:4",
      "text": "They wandered in the wilderness in a desert way. They found no city to live in.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:5",
      "text": "Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:6",
      "text": "Then they cried to Yahweh in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:7",
      "text": "He led them also by a straight way, that they might go to a city to live in.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:8",
      "text": "Let them praise Yahweh for his loving kindness, for his wonderful deeds to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:9",
      "text": "For he satisfies the longing soul. He fills the hungry soul with good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:10",
      "text": "Some sat in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and iron,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:11",
      "text": "because they rebelled against the words of God, and condemned the counsel of the Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:12",
      "text": "Therefore he brought down their heart with labor. They fell down, and there was no one to help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:13",
      "text": "Then they cried to Yahweh in their trouble, and he saved them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:14",
      "text": "He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and broke away their chains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:15",
      "text": "Let them praise Yahweh for his loving kindness, for his wonderful deeds to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:16",
      "text": "For he has broken the gates of bronze, and cut through bars of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:17",
      "text": "Fools are afflicted because of their disobedience, and because of their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:18",
      "text": "Their soul abhors all kinds of food. They draw near to the gates of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:19",
      "text": "Then they cry to Yahweh in their trouble, and he saves them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:20",
      "text": "He sends his word, and heals them, and delivers them from their graves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:21",
      "text": "Let them praise Yahweh for his loving kindness, for his wonderful deeds to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:22",
      "text": "Let them offer the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his deeds with singing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:23",
      "text": "Those who go down to the sea in ships, who do business in great waters,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:24",
      "text": "these see Yahweh’s deeds, and his wonders in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:25",
      "text": "For he commands, and raises the stormy wind, which lifts up its waves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:26",
      "text": "They mount up to the sky; they go down again to the depths. Their soul melts away because of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:27",
      "text": "They reel back and forth, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wits’ end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:28",
      "text": "Then they cry to Yahweh in their trouble, and he brings them out of their distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:29",
      "text": "He makes the storm a calm, so that its waves are still.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:30",
      "text": "Then they are glad because it is calm, so he brings them to their desired haven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:31",
      "text": "Let them praise Yahweh for his loving kindness, for his wonderful deeds for the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:32",
      "text": "Let them exalt him also in the assembly of the people, and praise him in the seat of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:33",
      "text": "He turns rivers into a desert, water springs into a thirsty ground,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:34",
      "text": "and a fruitful land into a salt waste, for the wickedness of those who dwell in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:35",
      "text": "He turns a desert into a pool of water, and a dry land into water springs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:36",
      "text": "There he makes the hungry live, that they may prepare a city to live in,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:37",
      "text": "sow fields, plant vineyards, and reap the fruits of increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:38",
      "text": "He blesses them also, so that they are multiplied greatly. He doesn’t allow their livestock to decrease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:39",
      "text": "Again, they are diminished and bowed down through oppression, trouble, and sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:40",
      "text": "He pours contempt on princes, and causes them to wander in a trackless waste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:41",
      "text": "Yet he lifts the needy out of their affliction, and increases their families like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:42",
      "text": "The upright will see it, and be glad. All the wicked will shut their mouths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.107.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:43",
      "text": "Whoever is wise will pay attention to these things. They will consider the loving kindnesses of Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
